@page "/changelog"
@layout PublicLayout

<PageTitle>Change Log — Nornis</PageTitle>

<article class="nornis-public-page">
    <div class="nornis-eyebrow">Change Log</div>
    <h1>What's new</h1>

    <section class="nornis-changelog-entry">
        <h2>July 2026</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Library: keep the sourcebooks, maps, and handouts your table actually uses as reference — indexed PDFs answer through the Loremaster with page citations, and nothing in the Library ever becomes canon.</li>
            <li>Reveal to the party: when the fiction gives a secret away, a GM ticks exactly what the party now learns — Nornis checks the reveal leaves nothing dangling and names what has to come with it. One-way, on purpose.</li>
            <li>Session Wrap-Up: after a session lands, a card surfaces what advanced, what's gone quiet, what could nest, and which new arcs need a home — each choice saved the moment you make it.</li>
            <li>Journey map: the party's trail across the map, session by session — drag the playhead to walk the route and surface what each stop meant.</li>
            <li>Public world sharing: give a world a public address and switch it on — visitors get a read-only view of party-visible material only: the codex, the timeline, and session notes. Nothing hidden ever appears.</li>
            <li>Ask suggestions are now drawn from your world's live state — active storylines, recent characters, unconfirmed rumors — instead of canned examples.</li>
            <li>The Loremaster understands follow-up questions in a conversation ("what is <em>he</em> suspected of?") and grounds them in earlier exchanges.</li>
            <li>Sharper truth-state handling in answers: rumors are attributed, disputed accounts show both sides, and GM-only knowledge is flagged as such.</li>
            <li>Cost dashboard gained a date-range filter for the by-operation, by-model, and by-user breakdowns.</li>
            <li>Confirmation prompts before destructive actions, clickable dashboard rows, capture shortcuts that pre-select the source type, and a full mobile pass.</li>
            <li>A public features page now lays out everything Nornis does, section by section.</li>
            <li>Canon, Costs, and Settings are no longer standalone pages — the accepted facts now live behind the codex, Ask, and Continuity Health, and Costs and Settings moved into the GM-only Admin page.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="nornis-changelog-entry">
        <h2>June 2026</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Ask the Loremaster launched: grounded answers with citations, confidence, and caveats.</li>
            <li>Continuity Health: a heuristic read on your record's consistency, completeness, groundedness, and recency.</li>
            <li>Review queue with accept / edit / reject on every AI-proposed change.</li>
            <li>Storylines, Canon, Sources, Artifacts, Costs, and Settings screens.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</article>
